			<title>Neil deGrasse Tyson - Space Chronicles</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://pointofinquiry.libsyn.com/neil-de-grasse-tyson-space-chronicles]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p>Host: Chris Mooney</p>
<p>This week, <em>Point of Inquiry</em> is thrilled to welcome back one of our most popular guests: Neil deGrasse Tyson, the famed astrophysicist and Frederick P. Rose Director of the&nbsp;Hayden Planetarium in New York City.</p>
<p>Last time we had him on, Dr. Tyson engaged in a wide ranging discussion about science communication and the place of science in America.</p>
<p>This time, we focus in on his new book&mdash;<em>Space Chronicles: Facing the Ultimate Frontier&mdash;</em>and his call for revitalizing NASA and letting it play a central role in reconnecting America and science.</p>
<p>Neil deGrasse Tyson is America's most pre-eminent science communicator. In addition to his work at the Hayden Planetarium and his books and television appearances, he is also the host of <em>Star Talk Radio</em>.</p>]]></description>
