        <item>
			<title>Alexander Zaitchik - Glenn Becks War on Reason</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://pointofinquiry.libsyn.com/alexander_zaitchik_glenn_beck_s_war_on_reason]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p>This week, the scope of <em>Point of Inquiry</em> expands to include politics and more particularly, the fount of misinformation that is Glenn Beck of Fox News. This TV and radio personality is ushering in a new reign of ignorance in our national discourse&mdash;and even has the gall to <a href="http://mediamatters.org/mmtv/200911250017" target="_blank">liken his efforts</a> to those of Martin Luther King, Jr.</p>
<p>But investigative journalist Alexander Zaitchick has pinned Beck to a wall with his new book <em>Common Nonsense: Glenn Beck and the Triumph of Ignorance</em>. He&rsquo;s even provoked Beck into denouncing him for practicing "despicable, yellow journalism." Coming from Beck, that&rsquo;s a compliment.</p>
<p>So tune in to learn more about how Beck has become a new icon of American irrationality&mdash;and just general cluelessness.</p>
<p>Alex Zaitchik is a freelance journalist living in Brooklyn, New York. He&rsquo;s contributed to <em>Salon.com</em>, <em>The Nation</em>, <em>Wired</em>, and many other distinguished publications. In the course of his career he has reported from locations ranging from Miami to Moscow, from Prague to Mexico City&mdash;and <em>Common Nonsense: Glenn Beck and the Triumph of Ignorance</em> is his first book.</p>]]></description>
