But critical, biographical, and editorial work on weird fiction is only 
one aspect of Joshi's multifaceted output. A prominent atheist, Joshi 
has published the anthology <i>Atheism: A Reader</i> and the 
anti-religious polemic, <i>God's Defenders: What They Believe and Why 
They Are Wrong</i>. He has also compiled an important anthology on race
 relations, <i>Documents of American Prejudice</i>. <br>
</p><p>
</p><p>
