			<title>Thomas J.J. Altizer - The Death of God</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://traffic.libsyn.com/pointofinquiry/POI_2010_04_02_Thomas_Altizer.mp3]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p>Thomas J.J. Altizer burst onto the religious scene in the 1960s with his  book <em>The Gospel of Christian Atheism</em>. He was one of the "Death  of God" theologians discussed in the famous TIME cover story, "Is God  Dead?" Altzier holds an M.A. in theology and Ph.D. in History of  Religions from the Universeity of Chicago. Now 83 years of age, Altizer  remains a Young Turk among radical theologians, insisting that only  Christians can be true atheists and must proclaim the death of God.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>In this conversation with Robert Price, Altizer delves into Death of God  theology. He explains the difference between saying "There is no God"  and "God is Dead." He discusses his interactions with other theologians  and what they thought of his work. Altizer gives his opinion of  contemporary public atheists and what he likes and dislikes about them.  He relates stories from his career involving other thinkers such as Paul  Tillich and Mircea Eliade&mdash;including a personal "initiation" experience.  He explains how he formerly debated evangelical Christians and how  Death of God theology can be used when doing so.&nbsp;</p>]]></description>
